  <a name="mmi-42164"></a>
  



      <div id="mmi-42164" class="scrolling-text-module colspan-4 rag measurable magic-module" data-event-category="magic_module/scrolling_text_module/42164" data-event-label="Scrolling Text Module 42164 (19/77)" data-instance-id="42164" data-id="105586">                  <div class="scrolling-text-module__inner" style="max-height: 240.0em" tabindex="0">
    
    <span style="font-size:18px"><strong><u>Women’s, Gender, and Sexuality Studies Grants</u><br>
<br>
The Isa and Avi Mehta Graduate Student Research Grant</strong></span><br>
Created through the generosity of Kavita Patel, Class of 1998, this fund provides research support for graduate students in the WGSS Certificate or PhD Programs.  WGSS graduate students may apply for up to $700 in support for research related to their work in the Certificate or PhD, including dissertation research.  Supported expenses may include travel* to archives; transcription of interviews; acquisition of inaccessible books or other materials (which may ultimately be offered to the Yale Library); assistance in research.  <br>
 <br>
<strong>The Spring 2025 deadline is Wednesday, February 26, 2025 by 11:59 PM. <a href="https://wgss.yale.edu/graduate-studies/isa-and-avi-mehta-graduate-student-research-fund-wgss-grant-application" target="_blank">Full information &amp; link to apply &gt;</a></strong><br>
<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size:18px"><strong>Women’s, Gender, and Sexuality Studies (WGSS) Graduate Student Research Funding Application</strong></span><br>
The WGSS Program is happy to announce a new funding resource for graduate students in the WGSS Certificate or Combined PhD program.  Up to seven WGSS graduate students per academic year will receive up to $700 each towards travel to an academic conference related to their work in the Certificate or Combined PhD program.  WGSS understands that those who do interdisciplinary scholarship often need to attend multiple conferences a year, and we are grateful to be able to support the professional development of our Certificate and PhD students.  Applications will be accepted twice per academic year, in February and October, with priority given to those who are presenting papers and who lack other sources of funding. <br>
 <br>
<strong>The Spring 2025 deadline is Wednesday, February 26, 2025 by 11:59 PM. <a href="https://wgss.yale.edu/funding/womens-gender-and-sexuality-studies-wgss-graduate-student-research-funding-application" target="_blank">Full information &amp; link to apply &gt;</a></strong>
</div>

