    <span style="font-size:18px"><strong>Visualize Science Competition 2025: Astrophysics Edition</strong></span><br>
<br>
An annual competition for teams of artists and scientists with a Yale affiliation to collaborate and create a conceptual model of a scientific concept in astrophysics (revealed at the start of the competition) and realize it in 2 or 3D format using provided materials.  No experience in astronomy or astrophysics is necessary for participants!<br>
<br>
Thursday, February 6, 2025<br>
6:00-8:30 p.m.<br>
KT 5th Floor Lounge<br>
<br>
<a href="http://forms.gle/uJD9S8D8KVj8jKZM8" target="_blank">Register &gt;</a><br>
<a href="http://wlab.yale.edu/visualize" target="_blank">More info at &gt;</a><br>
<br>
The Visualize Science contest is sponsored by Yale Wright Laboratory, the Yale Department of Astronomy, Yale Department of Physics, CCAM,YQI, and Yale University.
