<a href="https://www.instagram.com/ourhouseyale" target="_blank">OurHouse</a> is looking for BIPOC creatives (artists doing visual/sculptural installations, a live painting, projection, etc.) interested in collaborating with musicians/vocalists for a live and curated multimedia talent show. Imagine: a live painting, a harpist, a projection, a spoken word poem, a monologue, a breakdancer — performing with live music. If interested, submit ideas for any type of artistic performance or visual contribution to <a href="mailto:vivie.eteme@yale.edu" target="_blank"></a><a href="mailto:vivie.eteme@yale.edu">vivie.eteme@yale.edu</a> &amp; <a href="mailto:laura.zeng@yale.edu" target="_blank"></a><a href="mailto:laura.zeng@yale.edu">laura.zeng@yale.edu</a>, along with any examples of previous work <strong>by November 18.</strong>
