  <a name="mmi-41736"></a>
  



      <div id="mmi-41736" class="scrolling-text-module colspan-4 rag measurable magic-module" data-event-category="magic_module/scrolling_text_module/41736" data-event-label="Scrolling Text Module 41736 (37/77)" data-instance-id="41736" data-id="105156">                  <div class="scrolling-text-module__inner" style="max-height: 240.0em" tabindex="0">
    
    <span style="font-size:18px"><strong>A Call for Artists: En Plein Air Event on May 10 on the New Haven Green</strong></span><br>
<br>
The Garden Club of New Haven is celebrating its Centennial in 2025. During the year many events will occur throughout New Haven. On May 10, 2025 the Club is sponsoring a series of events on and around the New Haven Green to celebrate our 100 years. As part of this event we are hoping to have Connecticut artists on site to paint scenes of or around the Green. Other events occurring on this day are tours, a film, a flower show, floral design workshops, many community resource tables and food trucks.<br>
<br>
Paintings/art work will be exhibited and offered for sale at the DaSilva Gallery in Westville. The show will be curated by Gabe DaSilva, exhibited for the month of June with a reception on Thursday, June 5th. Twenty per cent of the sale will be donated to the Garden Club of New Haven, Fund for the Future, held at the Community Foundation for Greater New Haven. Eighty percent will be shared between the gallery and artists.<br>
<br>
Submissions- This is not a juried event. Artist can enter only 1 piece of art.<br>
In the event you cannot attend on May 10, you are welcome to paint another time, and bring your artwork to DaSilva Gallery on Saturday, May 31st between 10:00-4:00pm.<br>
<br>
<strong>To register and receive instructions, please <a href="mailto:janesnaider@gmail.com" target="_blank">contact Jane Snaider</a> by <u>March 1, 2025</u>. <a href="https://cdn.filestackcontent.com/6T6xytxnRgF7N483w9aW" target="_blank">Full information &gt;</a></strong>
</div>

