      <div id="mmi-43586" class="scrolling-text-module colspan-4 rag measurable magic-module" data-event-category="magic_module/scrolling_text_module/43586" data-event-label="Scrolling Text Module 43586 (48/77)" data-instance-id="43586" data-id="107171">                  <div class="scrolling-text-module__inner" style="max-height: 240.0em" tabindex="0">
    
    <span style="font-size:18px"><strong>Apply for The New Art School Modality’s “Notes from the Artist’s Studio Course”</strong></span><br>
<br>
The New Art School Modality’s upcoming offering, the “Notes from the Artist’s Studio Course”. This NASM course includes suggestions and lessons by artists with studio practices who share what they know and would want to impart to emerging makers about form and their approaches to art making and specific forms. <br>
 <br>
It will take place this Spring weekly on Fridays from 10 am - 12:30 pm EST beginning <strong>Friday, April 18, 2025 through May 9, 2025</strong>. As the past few have been, the course will be a virtual-in person hybrid. The in-person sessions will be on the Hauser &amp; Wirth, NY Gallery premises at 443 W 18th St, New York, NY 10011.<br>
 <br>
Faculty will include:<br>
<strong>Professor Iris Bernblum</strong>, whose practice includes sculpture, painting, drawing, video and performance<br>
<strong>Professor María Berrío</strong>, known for large scale works using Japanese paper and watercolor<br>
<strong>Professor Jeffrey Gibson</strong>, whose practice includes immersive, multi-sensory installations<br>
<strong>Professor Steffani Jemison</strong>, known for connecting mark-making, gesture, proposal, projection, movement, and document.<br>
<strong>Professor Dindga McCannon</strong>, known for paintings, quilts, prints and sculpture<br>
<strong>Professor Angel Otero</strong>, known for work in the field of abstract expressionism<br>
<a href="https://thenewartschoolmodality.com/faculty" target="_blank">You can learn more about the faculty here.</a><br>
 <br>
<strong>The deadline for this application is April 11th, 2025.</strong> <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScI7Flx4bWJD0WHaj6TttbnV0IDuo2ny0I3QKqjioyAcWqDrQ/viewform" target="_blank">Full information &amp; link to apply &gt;</a> <em>(Travel stipends are available for accepted SoA MFAs to travel to New York!)</em>
